article.headline: Delaware State 73, Jacksonville St. 62
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Caheem Broadus and Jahsha Blount each scored 16 points to lead Delaware State to a 73-62 victory over Jacksonville State on Monday night. The Hornets (2-5) broke Jacksonville State's 17-game home winning streak against non-conference opponents. There were eight lead changes and 11 ties before Delaware State went on a 17-6 run over the final 5 minutes. Delaware State was 15-of-22 from the field (68 percent) in the second half. Courtney Bradley had 15 points and seven rebounds for the Gamecocks (2-2), while Walker Russell had 10 points and five assists. B.J. Spencer scored 11 points for Jacksonville State and Dorien Brown added 10.
